gRPC receive request: the duration contains network and request parsing, etc.
acquire latch: lock the keys in memory to ensure serializability of write commands

process write: do conflict and constraint checks and generate changes to the underlying storage
async write: write the changes to raftstore, including replicating the changes and applying the changes to the RocksDB
gRPC send response: including response serialization and network
